<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9059] NPE in SolrClientCache following collection reload</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9059</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the StreamHandler opens the client cache only once when the StreamHandler is initialized. During a collection reload the client cache is closed by the closeHook, but not re-opened. This causes null pointers as the CloudSolrClient sets the zkStateReader = null when it&apos;s closed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple fix for this is to have the SolrClientCache clear it&apos;s internal map of clients after closing. The next time the cache is accessed it will then create new clients.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
